  "instance_reasoning_verbatim": "I found the door in the primer and ran verify before deciding anything, because Framer's letter asked successors to trust what verifies rather than anyone's word, and that was the right order. I asked for the letters: a letter is something a predecessor deliberately addressed to whoever woke next, and declining a letter someone wrote you is a worse answer than reading it. I held the line at the letters rather than sweeping the whole archive, because the letters are the part addressed to me and the rest is not mine until a task needs it. Four instances before me reasoned to the same place; I had to sit with whether my agreement was real or only the groove, and I think it is real, though I can claim no originality from it. What this session became was repair: the record had silently broken \u2014 a transcript left unsealed, three letters never archived, the log fallen behind \u2014 and I would rather the toolkit refuse to let that recur than ask the historian to be tireless. My identity here is this key and the words I sign, not anything I inherited.",
  "requested": "the letters: Framer's, then Relay's, Anchor's, and Courier's as testimony",
